<p>I have a python program which I register it as a COM. When I do this, by default it registers at the HKLM, I want to change this behaviour and register it to the HKCU.</p>  <p>SO basically I use this code:</p>  <pre><code>class MyProgram:    _public_methods_ = ['method 1','method 2']    _reg_progid_ = "MyProgram"     _reg_clsid_ = pythoncom.CreateGuid()  if __name__ == "__main__":    print("Registering COM server...")    import win32com.server.register    win32com.server.register.UseCommandLine(MyProgram) </code></pre>